window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A stolen throne. A forbidden sea. A sword that could save—or destroy—it all.</b></p><p>Princess Tirzana of the Never Sea has one job: protect the legendary sword Excalibur. But when two strangers crash into her underwater realm—one claiming to be the exiled King Arthur—Tirzana’s destiny collides with legends she’s never believed.</p><p>Above the waves, Arthur fights to reclaim his kingdom from his ruthless sister Morgan. Below, Tirzana wrestles with duty, freedom, and a growing attraction to the mysterious inventor at Arthur’s side—Merlin.</p><p>As war brews between sea and surface, Tirzana must decide what she’s willing to risk to uncover the truth… and whether the myths of old might hold the key to saving them all.</p><p>Perfect for fans of <b>fairytale retellings, Arthurian legends, steampunk fantasy, and slow-burn romance</b>, <i>Terror in Wonderland</i> plunges readers into a world of <b>magic, rebellion, underwater kingdoms, and chosen destiny</b>.</p>"; 
